title: For Sale:  FNP-45 with case and three magazines
postcontent: This pistol is in great shape. It comes in the original case with the three original magazines that came with it-- 2 ea 14 round and 1 ea 15 round. The magazines don't seem to agree with white box ball ammo very well. You can do a Google search if you want to know more about it. The pistol is a great design though. Fully ambidextrous with no modifications--safety, slide catch, and magazine release. It's single or double action. You can leave one in the pipe with the hammer back and safety on, or use the decocker to safely move the hammer forward before res-afing. Either way it will fire once the safety is disengaged. Color is flat dark earth for the frame and flat gray/black for the slide. Backstrap is also able to be changed out to fit your hand better. I have the curved one on currently, but there's also a flat backstrap included.Willing to ship through authorized FFL. Buyer pays shipping.
